Here are both approaches using Shell navigation with `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel.

## 1. Route Registration (AppShell.xaml.cs)

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

## 2. Navigate from ProductListPage

```csharp
// Approach A: Pass product ID as a query string
async void OnProductSelected(object sender, SelectionChangedEventArgs e)
{
    if (e.CurrentSelection.FirstOrDefault() is Product product)
    {
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?id={product.Id}");
    }
}

// Approach B: Pass the full Product object
async void OnProductSelected(object sender, SelectionChangedEventArgs e)
{
    if (e.CurrentSelection.FirstOrDefault() is Product product)
    {
        var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        {
            { "product", product }
        };
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
    }
}
```

## 3. Receive Data via IQueryAttributable (ViewModel)

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string parameter from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("id", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID
            _ = LoadProductAsync(ProductId);
        }

        // Approach B: full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }

    private async Task LoadProductAsync(string id)
    {
        // fetch from your data service
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string (`?id=...`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| Data type | String only | Any object |
| Serialization | Values become strings | No serialization needed |
| Best for | Simple IDs, small values | Complex/large objects |
| Deep-link friendly | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |

**Gotchas:** Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions, and make sure `productdetails` is registered via `Routing.RegisterRoute` before navigating.
